<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53115m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53115m">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53115m"> 115(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Eliza Ryves hermit of Snowden</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>RYVES, ELIZABETH</mark>, author; b. 1750; cheated of her property, she went to London to live by her pen; wrote poems, plays, translations, and one novel, <mark><cite>The Hermit of Snowdon</cite></mark>, depicting her own sorrows; Isaac Disraeli wrote touchingly of her efforts in <cite>Calamities of Authors</cite>; d. 1797. <small> John S. Crone, <a name="JSCD1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JSCD1"><cite title="source">A Concise Dictionary of Irish Biography</cite></a> (Apr 1928) 225</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
